# NEOJAGARÔTH
  * Jagarôth with thematic voice system

## Outer Structure summary
  * Comparative system
	* OUT- (exceed)
	* UNDER- (fall short)
  * Transfer system
	* DAT- (recipient core)
	* FOR- (benefactive)
	* FROM- (source)
  * Social/relational system
	* WITH- (Comitative)
	* AGAINST- (oppositional)
	* OVER- (dominance)
  * Cognitive/internal system
	* IN- (internalization)

## Design constraints
  * Prefixes must belong to exactly one domain
      * comparative
      * transfer
      * social
      * cognitive
  * Only one (1) domain may control core argument structure at a time
  
## fully worked sentence paradigm
  * Neutral baseline
  Kak.NOM give money.ACC church.DAT Tam.OBL
  dregâl Kak yurot kirkôdh Tamist
  Kak gives money to the church, Tam is just there.
  ==> comparison implied pragmatically
  
  * WITH- frame 
	- (comitative voice) 
	- (co-participant emphasis)
	
	Kak WITH-give money.ACC church.DAT Tam.OBL
	weg-dregâl Kak yurot kirkôð Tamaþ
	
	WHY? WHY isn't TAM promoted to ACC?
	
	Kak WITH-give Tam.ACC kirk.DAT money.OBL
	
		* FOR- frame
		- benefactive focus
